@plane z=1 label="Ep 1-2 Eliminations"
# Rounds 1 & 2 — The Beach Purge

## Episode 1 Elimination
**Challenge:** 72-hour no-phone survival. Who breaks first?

> "Dexx lasted 11 hours before stealing a producer's satellite phone."
> — field notes

**Eliminated:** Dexx *(voted off: 61% audience, cited "exhausting energy")*
**Drama:** Kade and Soleil form an alliance nobody believes will last.

---

## Episode 2 Elimination
**Challenge:** Collaborative content shoot — only one gets the ring light.

> Margaux redirected the entire shoot to center herself. Tomas documented it on a disposable camera he found in his bag.

**Eliminated:** Rafe Dunmore *(prepper skills irrelevant; zero charisma on camera)*
**Twist:** Tomas's disposable camera footage aired as a mid-episode short. *Audience loved it.*

---

### Bracket Status After Ep 2
~~Dexx~~ · ~~Rafe Dunmore~~ · 14 remain → [[z=2|see Ep 3-4]]

@plane z=2 label="Ep 3-4 Eliminations"
# Rounds 3 & 4 — The Tribal Content Drop

## Episode 3 Elimination
**Challenge:** Each castmember posts ONE piece of content from the island. Engagement tracked live.

| Top Performers | Engagement Rate |
|----------------|----------------|
| Chidinma Eze | 22.4% |
| Brecken Vale | 18.9% |
| Tomas Creed | 17.1% *(disposable cam again)* |

**Eliminated:** Yuna Sato *(bottom engagement; island has no unboxing product to unbox)*
**Moment:** Beau Strider roped an actual pig for content. It escaped. Three cameras followed the pig.

---

## Episode 4 Elimination
**Challenge:** Tribal council — housemates vote, NOT audience.

**Political fallout:** Kade-Soleil alliance collapses when Soleil nominates Kade "for his growth."
**Eliminated:** Pax Holloway *(wrong show for their energy — they said so gracefully)*

> "This is a competition for people who want to be perceived. I want to be understood. Wrong venue, good snacks."
> — Pax's exit interview

---

~~Dexx~~ · ~~Rafe~~ · ~~Yuna~~ · ~~Pax~~ · 12 remain → [[z=3|see Ep 5-6]]

@plane z=3 label="Ep 5-6 Eliminations"
# Rounds 5 & 6 — The Merge Crisis

## Episode 5 Elimination
**Challenge:** Pairs challenge. Worst-performing pair: one goes home.

**Pair drama index (producer notes):**

- Brecken + Nadia — *competent, boring, good TV only in retrospect*
- Kade + Vesper — *Vesper recorded Kade crying, posted it. Audience split 50/50*
- Margaux + Ozzy — *Ozzy cooked, Margaux took credit, Ozzy let her*
- Chidinma + Beau — *unexpected best friends. Zero drama. Producers nervous.*

**Eliminated:** Lena Voss *(her dark academia arc required a library; island has none)*

---

## Episode 6 Elimination — THE BLINDSIDE
**Challenge:** Producers introduce a "Legacy Round." Past eliminees return to vote ONE person back in.

> Dexx returned, immediately campaigned for Kade's elimination.
> Rafe returned, said nothing, voted Margaux.

**Voted back in:** Tomas Creed *(unanimous among returnees — "he saw us clearly")*
**Eliminated:** Kade Rutherford *(Soleil, Vesper, AND Dexx's ghost vote aligned)*

> "The algorithm decides who wins. I AM the algorithm." — Kade, at elimination

~~Dexx~~ · ~~Rafe~~ · ~~Yuna~~ · ~~Pax~~ · ~~Lena~~ · ~~Kade~~ · 10 remain → [[z=4|see Ep 7 semifinals]]

@plane z=4 label="Ep 7 Semifinal"
# Episode 7 — Final Five Bracket

## Semifinal Eliminations (Double Elimination Week)

### The Final 10 → Final 5
**Format:** Head-to-head audience vote, 24 hours per matchup, live bracket on show website.

```
Brecken Vale    ──┐
                  ├─ Brecken (51%)
Tomas Creed    ──┘

Soleil Marsh   ──┐
                  ├─ Soleil (58%)
Beau Strider   ──┘

Margaux Bellini ─┐
                  ├─ Chidinma (71%) ← biggest margin of season
Chidinma Eze   ──┘

Vesper Quinn   ──┐
                  ├─ Vesper (55%)
Ozzy Tan       ──┘

Pilar Okonkwo  ──┐
                  ├─ Nadia (53%) ← closest vote of season
Nadia Frost    ──┘
```

---

